    "bio": "Abimbola Oluwatobi MAKINDE, PhD. Dr Makinde earned her PhD in Social Work from the University of Benin and has over seven years of academic and research experience in Social Work. Has an MSc. in Sociology and BSc. in Social Work from the University of Lagos, Nigeria. Research interests centre on school social work, child and family welfare and medical social work. Her recent publications include Correlates of Non-Adherence to Preventive Breast Cancer Screenings among women in Lagos State (African Social Science and Humanities Journal, 2024) and several authored and co-authored peer-reviewed articles such as HIV/AIDS voluntary counseling and testing: knowledge, attitude and practice among University of Lagos Undergraduates (African Social Science and Humanities Journal, 2024) and The Role of Neighbourhood Houses in Community Service and Sustainable Development in Makoko, Lagos State (Readings in UN-Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) and the Lagos Region, Faculty of Social Sciences, University of Lagos, 2020). ",
